  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Comprehensive mesh-refinement studies, turbulence-model sensitivity analyses, and bench-level validation against published FDA pump data collectively support a Medium assurance finding. All acceptance criteria were reviewed by an independent credibility assessment team prior to the Accepted decision.",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cpb-hemolysis-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cpb-hemolysis-claim-001",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/morrison-cfd-hemolysis-v3",
