      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental operating conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid temperature, hematocrit) documented and matched to simulation boundary conditions within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Published FDA experimental dataset provides flow rate and rotational speed for all five operating points. However, hematocrit and blood temperature during the original FDA experiments were not reported in the primary reference. Simulation assumed nominal values (Hct = 40%, T = 37°C) without experimental confirmation. This gap means the test-conditions factor achieves only Gradation 1 against the Gradation 2 requirement — a shortfall that was noted in the internal review but was not escalated to the decision record. The overall assessment proceeded to an Accepted outcome and Medium assurance declaration without formally resolving this factor deficit."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
