      "rationale": "NIH predictions fell within 18% of experimental mean at four operating points. The fifth point (3500 RPM, 6 L/min) showed 21% deviation, attributed to documented boundary-layer separation; bias direction is conservative (over-prediction of hemolysis). Overall output comparison assessed at Gradation 2."
